data.title: BBC Programme Index
data.text:
Peter Simon introduces a bumper package of Saturday entertainment starting with Ovide

Between the mad marshes and the Venetian Jetty, the Virgin Forest and the mysterious caverns, there's no shortage of adventures for Ovide the duckbilled platypus.

Just for Laughs

8.40am ChuckleVision starring the Chuckle Brothers with Billy Butler.

Angling for success, Paul and Barry spin a line and take up fishing. And Billy Butler tells the tale of Slimeball Simon. Writer JOHN SAYLE

Director JOHN NORTHOVER Producer MARTIN HUGHES BBC North West

9.00am Going Live! with Sarah Greene and Phillip Schofield.

Featuring heat one of the BBC Young Entertainer of the Year competition, film previews with special guest

Mark Hamill.

Cartoon action with Muppet Babies and Droids. There's music from Yazz and Def Leppard and really wild visitors with Terry Nutkins. Going Live! gives you the chance to nominate candidates for Comic Relief's gunk tank.

Trevor and Simon take Anthea Turner to meet some Vikings. There's Press Conference,

Soapbox plus Live Line and all sorts. Join the Going Live! gang at 9.00am and find out more! Editor CHRIS BELLINGER

Your letter

Was only the start of it, One letter,

And now you're a part of it. If you have an entertaining and original secret dream that you would like 'fixed' for yourself or as a surprise for someone else, maybe

Jimmy Savile can help. Lighting BRENDAN CARR Sound JIM CADMAN

Designer ROSEMARY HESTER

Series producer ROGER ORDISH Produced and directed by STANLEY APPEL

Payback

A female cop is wounded in a professional hit which kills her partner and the Grand Jury witness they are protecting. Jordan, the policewoman, is unable to remember the event or the face of the killer and calls on Jack Killian 's friendship as she struggles with the guilt over her partner's death. But the man who stands to lose most by her living wants the loose ends tied up ...

Written by DEBORAH ARAKEUAN Directed by KEVIN HOOKS

Overwhelmed by the senseless horrors of the Vietnam War, newspaperman

John Converse decides to register his opposition by means of a desperate act. He draws his buddy Ray Hicks and his wife Marge into a scheme to ship a consignment of heroin to the United States. Their plan backfires and Converse finds the violence of Vietnam has been destructively brought home.
